paraphrased:
Polycarp is organizing a Berland ICPC regional event. There are $n$ universities in Berland, numbered from 1 to $n$. He knows all the competitive programmers in the region: there are $n$ students, where the $i$?th student is enrolled at university $u_i$ and has programming skill $s_i$.

Polycarp must choose a team size $k$. If he selects $k$, then from each university:

* The $k$ students with the highest skill $s_i$ form the first team;
* The next $k$ strongest form the second team;
* And so on;
* If fewer than $k$ students remain, they cannot form another team.

Some universities may send zero teams. The strength of the region is defined as the total skill of all members across all formed teams; if no teams are formed, the strength is 0.

Compute the region’s strength for every choice of $k$ from 1 to $n$.
